1
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:03,104
It was in my pocket.

2
00:01:07,776 --> 00:01:09,819
It's clean. It's just a little crumpled.

3
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:15,200
What a surprise

4
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:17,160
to see you carry this around.

5
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:20,330
Since I live alone, I should carry it
around to look better.

6
00:01:20,413 --> 00:01:21,623
That's what my mom told me.

7
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:25,794
It'll make you look worse
if you carry it around like this.

8
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,629
You should iron it or something.

9
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:30,757
I'm usually good at ironing,

10
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:33,885
but my mom took the iron with her.

11
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:36,721
She's living in the countryside
because of her work.

12
00:01:40,183 --> 00:01:41,768
That explains it.

13
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:43,895
That's why your uniform and clothes

14
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:46,189
always seemed all wrinkled up and dirty.

15
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:48,066
Since you don't have an iron?

16
00:01:49,818 --> 00:01:51,194
It's not that dirty.

17
00:01:52,487 --> 00:01:53,780
They said it looked okay.

18
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:56,991
Who said that?

19
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:58,368
What?

20
00:02:01,412 --> 00:02:02,831
The people at school.

21
00:02:03,414 --> 00:02:04,541
The girls.

22
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:11,089
Gosh, you pretended not to know
anything and be indifferent,

23
00:02:11,172 --> 00:02:14,134
but you were actually enjoying
what the girls were saying, right?

24
00:02:14,592 --> 00:02:16,886
No, that's not what I meant.

25
00:02:17,345 --> 00:02:19,764
I didn't want to hear them,

26
00:02:19,889 --> 00:02:21,808
but I couldn't help overhearing.

27
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:24,269
And they all have loud voices, you know.

28
00:02:24,769 --> 00:02:25,854
So that's why...

29
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:39,701
How come you're not asking?

30
00:02:40,869 --> 00:02:41,703
What?

31
00:02:44,038 --> 00:02:45,373
About what's wrong.

32
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:48,334
Why I was walking around like this.

33
00:02:52,255 --> 00:02:53,798
How come you're not asking me?

34
00:02:57,051 --> 00:02:58,511
Why I'm such a mess?

35
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:06,060
You probably got into a fight again.

36
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,354
Again?

37
00:03:09,939 --> 00:03:11,816
I don't go around fighting and stuff.

38
00:03:13,109 --> 00:03:14,777
If you didn't fight, then what?

39
00:03:14,986 --> 00:03:16,905
Did you work out? Play a game?

40
00:03:21,784 --> 00:03:24,370
Let's just say
it was some kind of matchup.

41
00:03:26,831 --> 00:03:28,750
Are you sure you weren't beaten up?

42
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:30,418
What do you take me for?

43
00:03:31,544 --> 00:03:33,671
I can't get into detail right now,

44
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:35,256
but anyway, that's what happened.

45
00:03:37,884 --> 00:03:39,385
Aren't you going to answer that?

46
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:48,853
Oh, right.

47
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:57,737
-Yes?
-Hey! Where are you?

48
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:14,003
Hey, how could you forget
to go to your part-time job?

49
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:16,839
I was caught up in an emergency.

50
00:04:29,727 --> 00:04:32,272
Wait, why are you taking me with you?

51
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:34,482
It's too far to walk,
and it might rain again.

52
00:04:34,565 --> 00:04:35,650
Hold on tight.

53
00:04:35,817 --> 00:04:36,818
Okay.

54
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:48,371
Why did you send me an unfinished script?

55
00:04:48,496 --> 00:04:50,290
"Not because I'm afraid of ghosts..."

56
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:52,458
What comes after that? Tell me.

57
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,336
Aren't you going to answer me?

58
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:35,418
Hello.

59
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:37,128
What are you two doing?

60
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:40,423
Yeong-bae, are you late
because you were flirting with...

61
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:43,384
What's wrong with your face?
Who did that to you?

62
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:46,345
-Did you do it?
-What?

63
00:05:47,388 --> 00:05:50,016
No, I fell off my bike.

64
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:51,267
Both of you?

65
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:52,518
-No.
-No.

66
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:55,855
You two are dating, aren't you?

67
00:05:56,564 --> 00:05:57,565
-No.
-No.

68
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:09,243
Soo-bin.

69
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:11,079
Hey, Hwi-yeong.

70
00:06:11,412 --> 00:06:12,580
Where were you?

71
00:06:12,914 --> 00:06:14,582
Your mom was really worried.

72
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:16,334
Did you go to my house?

73
00:06:16,918 --> 00:06:18,169
Yes. To go to the academy together.

74
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:19,712
Congratulations on passing the test.

75
00:06:20,922 --> 00:06:22,673
Do I have to go today?

76
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:25,009
Of course. You need to start right away.

77
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:29,430
Jun-u, did you get into a fight again?

78
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:31,390
Right? I was right.

79
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:34,894
Tell me if you're in trouble. Anytime.

80
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:37,605
Why?

81
00:06:40,316 --> 00:06:41,734
Since we're in the same class.

82
00:06:42,151 --> 00:06:44,362
We should help each other out
whenever we're in trouble.

83
00:06:48,324 --> 00:06:50,743
I'm not sure. I don't want to.

84
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:55,998
Suit yourself. See you tomorrow.

85
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:58,584
-Let's go, Soo-bin.
-Okay.

86
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,717
Jun-u.

87
00:07:07,468 --> 00:07:09,554
Send me the last part of the script, okay?

88
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:18,146
Hey, Yeong-bae.
Those two are dating, right?

89
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,481
No.

90
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:23,818
What are you talking about?

91
00:07:24,152 --> 00:07:26,863
That little girl is so lucky.

92
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:29,866
Hey, go and get changed now.

93
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:43,880
No, I didn't walk in the rain that much.

94
00:07:45,381 --> 00:07:48,968
I just walked around here and there.

95
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:52,346
Okay, Mom.

96
00:08:06,777 --> 00:08:09,071
I brought your clothes. Change into them.

97
00:08:10,698 --> 00:08:13,326
What's wrong with my mom?
She didn't have to ask you.

98
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:14,827
I asked her first.

99
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:17,455
She was worried you might be
walking in the rain.

100
00:08:19,248 --> 00:08:20,458
Is there somewhere you can change?

101
00:08:20,541 --> 00:08:23,169
Oh, it's okay. I'm fine.

102
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:26,589
Go and change. What if you catch a cold?

103
00:08:33,721 --> 00:08:34,722
Look.

104
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:40,019
It's dry, right? I don't have to change.

105
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:45,525
But the thing is, Hwi-yeong...

106
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:49,362
Don't do things like this.
It makes me a bit uncomfortable.

107
00:08:50,279 --> 00:08:51,489
Why do you feel uncomfortable?

108
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:53,574
I brought it because I wanted to.

109
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:58,079
Well, we'll be late. Let's hurry.

110
00:08:58,329 --> 00:09:00,873
Let's go, Hwi-yeong.
Don't forget your stuff.

111
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:06,462
CHOE JUN-U

112
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:34,282
I told you to send me the part after
this. Why haven't you sent it yet?

113
00:09:42,873 --> 00:09:45,126
And translate what you wrote earlier

114
00:09:45,209 --> 00:09:46,711
into English and send it to me.

115
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:49,088
I won't say anything even if
it's not good, so just send it.

116
00:09:49,171 --> 00:09:50,464
It'll help you study.

117
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:51,924
"It'll help you study"?

118
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:57,305
Right, she's in the top tier in English.

119
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,772
All right. As you guys just saw,
we can prove that the sine rule

120
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:08,983
is always valid for acute, right,

121
00:10:09,066 --> 00:10:11,736
and obtuse-angled triangles.

122
00:10:11,819 --> 00:10:15,031
In summary, this is the formula
you guys will have to use.

123
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:17,992
The length of one side divided by
the sine value equals the diameter

124
00:10:18,075 --> 00:10:20,036
of the circumscribed circle.

125
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:22,121
Okay, let's put it to use right away.

126
00:10:22,204 --> 00:10:24,040
Who wants to solve this question?

127
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:28,377
Hwi-yeong, do you want to try?

128
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:36,719
-Sure.
-Were you distracted?

129
00:10:36,886 --> 00:10:37,928
What's with you today?

130
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:40,264
Mr. Son, I guess he's having

131
00:10:40,348 --> 00:10:42,600
a hard time concentrating
because his girlfriend

132
00:10:42,683 --> 00:10:44,810
has graced us with her presence today.

133
00:10:44,894 --> 00:10:46,854
Gosh, it's a big problem.

134
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:49,482
This is no good.

135
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:51,609
What should we do about this?

136
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:53,944
Mr. Son. Instead of him,

137
00:10:54,987 --> 00:10:57,239
since I don't have a girlfriend,

138
00:10:58,199 --> 00:10:59,367
I'll try solving it.

139
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:00,826
Okay, give it a shot.

140
00:11:02,244 --> 00:11:04,246
Why do you think
that you don't have a girlfriend?

141
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:07,792
-Never mind. I'm sorry.
-Ro-mi, Soo-bin is at our academy.

142
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:09,335
Erase this first.

143
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:12,421
I'm back.

144
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:29,688
I'm home.

145
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:33,901
Yes.

146
00:11:35,486 --> 00:11:36,904
Did you have a good day?

147
00:11:37,696 --> 00:11:39,240
Was the class okay?

148
00:11:39,323 --> 00:11:41,617
Yes, it was all right.

149
00:11:42,243 --> 00:11:44,870
Mom, what happened?

150
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:45,955
Did you hurt your head?

151
00:11:46,038 --> 00:11:48,457
I bumped my head
when I was running after you earlier.

152
00:11:52,586 --> 00:11:53,546
I'm sorry.

153
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:57,258
It was quite upsetting for me to see you

154
00:11:57,341 --> 00:12:01,178
being like that
in front of Hwi-yeong's mom.

155
00:12:02,012 --> 00:12:03,305
Soo-bin.

156
00:12:04,306 --> 00:12:05,766
I know...

157
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:09,270
that I pester you so much.

158
00:12:10,187 --> 00:12:11,981
I also know that I shouldn't.

159
00:12:12,606 --> 00:12:15,609
I always tell myself to let go
of my greed, but it's not easy.

160
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,654
You're my one and only daughter,

161
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:22,032
my baby whom I love the most
in the whole wide world.

162
00:12:23,451 --> 00:12:25,703
"What if she graduates
from a mediocre university?

163
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:29,123
And what if people look down
on her because of that?

164
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:32,751
What if she can't get a nice husband?

165
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:35,504
What if she can't afford
to live in Gangnam?

166
00:12:35,671 --> 00:12:39,633
What if she struggles?"
I can't stop worrying.

167
00:12:43,637 --> 00:12:44,680
Mom.

168
00:12:45,514 --> 00:12:47,433
Gosh, lie on your back.

169
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,394
This is why your shoulders
are always so tense.

170
00:12:54,064 --> 00:12:55,483
I'll study hard.

171
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:57,693
Don't worry too much.

172
00:13:10,539 --> 00:13:12,166
I didn't get hurt for nothing after all.

173
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:16,045
Gosh.

174
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:42,154
Sent you the English version.
Revise it for me please.

175
00:13:47,117 --> 00:13:49,828
About the part at the end...
I'm still thinking.

176
00:13:56,877 --> 00:13:57,878
My gosh.

177
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:01,590
Jun-u's English is seriously bad.

178
00:14:02,091 --> 00:14:03,467
What do I do?

179
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:06,220
Oh, my goodness.

180
00:14:07,888 --> 00:14:09,557
I can see that he tried his best.

181
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:21,569
It's relatively good.

182
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:23,028
I made a few changes.

183
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:25,489
This isn't "a few."

184
00:14:26,574 --> 00:14:27,700
How embarrassing.

185
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:31,829
Memorize the whole thing.
We'll go over it together tomorrow.

186
00:14:31,912 --> 00:14:33,539
You can't sleep until you memorize it.

187
00:14:46,635 --> 00:14:47,678
That explains it.

188
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:50,055
That's why your uniform and clothes

189
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:52,683
always seemed all wrinkled up and dirty.

190
00:14:52,766 --> 00:14:54,268
Since you don't have an iron?

191
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:08,073
TO REMOVE WRINKLES WITHOUT AN IRON

192
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:19,251
It was in my pocket.

193
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:45,421
Why is Mom calling so early?

194
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:16,994
-Hi, Mom.
-Good morning, Jun-u.

195
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:19,288
-Are you washing up?
-Yes, my eyes are burning. Hurry.

196
00:17:19,371 --> 00:17:20,330
Okay, Jun-u.

197
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:21,999
Don't forget to eat breakfast.

198
00:17:22,082 --> 00:17:23,917
-Breakfast, okay.
-Put on the uniform,

199
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:26,462
-and don't forget the handkerchief.
-The handkerchief? Got it.

200
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:28,630
Mom, I have to go. My eyes are burning.

201
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:31,175
All right. I love you, my baby.

202
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:32,885
-Okay, bye.
-Have a good day.

203
00:17:33,093 --> 00:17:34,178
Okay.

204
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,865
Jeong-hu, are you all right?

205
00:18:04,249 --> 00:18:06,960
Please leave a message after the tone.

206
00:18:21,266 --> 00:18:22,309
Hi.

207
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:25,938
Jun-u?

208
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,899
Choe Jun-u. Come here.

209
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:31,401
Choe-- Hey.

210
00:18:47,876 --> 00:18:49,086
I bet you weren't expecting this.

211
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:51,630
What's up with that mask?

212
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:57,177
You're such a great actor.

213
00:18:57,261 --> 00:18:59,763
Are you in a boy band or what? Come here.

214
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:01,306
Stand still. Take that off.

215
00:19:02,891 --> 00:19:04,101
What happened to your face?

216
00:19:05,853 --> 00:19:07,354
-Mr. Oh!
-Hello.

217
00:19:08,105 --> 00:19:08,981
Hello.

218
00:19:09,106 --> 00:19:11,441
He caught a cold in this heat.

219
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:13,318
-Great.
-Okay.

220
00:19:13,402 --> 00:19:14,653
Have a nice day.

221
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:20,993
Hey. What happened?
Did you get in a fight?

222
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:22,244
When? Where? With whom?

223
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:25,289
No. I fell off my bike.

224
00:19:25,998 --> 00:19:27,207
You fell off your bike

225
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:30,002
and got these small wounds
on your eye, lip, and cheek?

226
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:31,670
You don't want to say, is that it?

227
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:37,134
Fine. Well, nothing was reported
to the school,

228
00:19:37,217 --> 00:19:38,886
so it must not be anything big.

229
00:19:39,511 --> 00:19:40,637
Are you sure you're okay?

230
00:19:41,138 --> 00:19:43,390
Yes. I'm sorry.

231
00:19:43,765 --> 00:19:46,185
Cover it up well and cough a lot.

232
00:19:46,268 --> 00:19:48,604
Okay. Hi, Hwi-yeong, Gi-tae.

233
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:49,855
-Hello.
-Hello.

234
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:53,483
Why did you have to catch a cold?

235
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:10,250
They got scared when the cops showed up.

236
00:20:11,501 --> 00:20:12,920
They'll do it right next time.

237
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:19,009
They won't do anything stupid, right?

238
00:20:21,136 --> 00:20:23,555
I don't think they will. Don't worry.

239
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:25,015
What if they will?

240
00:20:31,104 --> 00:20:32,147
Don't worry.

241
00:20:33,899 --> 00:20:35,317
You have me.

242
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:43,992
SEARCH

243
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:46,954
BYEONGMUN HIGH SCHOOL

244
00:20:47,037 --> 00:20:50,415
Are you having carrots for lunch again?

245
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:52,334
That's right.

246
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:54,086
You'll turn into a rabbit.

247
00:20:54,169 --> 00:20:56,463
-O-je. When are we going to practice?
-Oh, hi.

248
00:20:56,546 --> 00:20:58,006
Later.

249
00:20:58,131 --> 00:20:59,925
Why? Can't we do it now?

250
00:21:00,008 --> 00:21:01,051
Later.

251
00:21:07,224 --> 00:21:08,058
Hi.

252
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:12,896
Hey. Hi.

253
00:21:13,897 --> 00:21:16,483
That will draw more attention
from the teachers.

254
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:21,780
That must hurt.

255
00:21:22,489 --> 00:21:23,490
Not at all.

256
00:21:25,826 --> 00:21:28,287
Did you practice English a lot?

257
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:33,875
A little.

258
00:21:43,093 --> 00:21:44,553
A little won't be enough.

259
00:21:56,857 --> 00:21:59,484
I washed it. Thanks.

260
00:22:05,198 --> 00:22:07,909
If you do that, it'll be wrinkled.

261
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:10,120
I ironed it nicely.

262
00:22:29,890 --> 00:22:30,807
Good.

263
00:22:33,852 --> 00:22:37,564
Well... You said you had no iron,
but you ironed it nicely.

264
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:49,993
Hey. So...

265
00:22:50,077 --> 00:22:52,120
I worked on our test a little...

266
00:22:52,204 --> 00:22:54,706
Pil-sang. Get lost.

267
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:57,667
Okay. I will.

268
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:10,055
What are you doing?

269
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:12,099
Darn it. Just go back to studying.

270
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:23,318
Jun-u. Your face...

271
00:23:24,444 --> 00:23:26,279
-Are you okay?
-Are you all right?

272
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:30,367
Hey, Jun-u.

273
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:31,868
You must have gotten into a fight.

274
00:23:31,952 --> 00:23:33,245
Who was it?

275
00:23:33,328 --> 00:23:35,288
Our neighborhood has been quiet lately.

276
00:23:35,455 --> 00:23:37,666
Right, Pil-sang? Pil-sang...

277
00:23:38,458 --> 00:23:40,710
Hey. Jun-u must have been beaten up.

278
00:23:41,419 --> 00:23:43,547
Right? That's why he's wearing
a mask, right?

279
00:23:43,630 --> 00:23:46,174
-Yes.
-I'm not even surprised.

280
00:23:46,341 --> 00:23:47,592
I don't think so.

281
00:23:47,676 --> 00:23:50,178
I heard he fell off his bike.

282
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:51,304
No, no.

283
00:23:52,347 --> 00:23:53,223
I doubt that.

284
00:23:55,183 --> 00:23:56,017
Soo-bin.

285
00:23:56,726 --> 00:23:58,186
Yes, Ro-mi?

286
00:23:58,311 --> 00:24:00,105
I hear you're taking Mr. Son's classes.

287
00:24:00,188 --> 00:24:02,649
-For real?
-Did you pass the level test?

288
00:24:03,066 --> 00:24:04,151
I knew it.

289
00:24:04,234 --> 00:24:06,528
I hear it's not easy
to get a chance to take the test.

290
00:24:07,154 --> 00:24:08,488
How did you get to take it?

291
00:24:09,573 --> 00:24:10,782
What happened was...

292
00:24:10,866 --> 00:24:12,117
I recommended her.

293
00:24:12,325 --> 00:24:14,286
I thought she was qualified.

294
00:24:14,578 --> 00:24:17,080
Did you even take the level test?

295
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:20,834
I did. Ro-mi, let's talk--

296
00:24:20,917 --> 00:24:23,253
Hwi-yeong, can we have a word?

297
00:24:26,047 --> 00:24:28,592
Later. I need to do this now.

298
00:24:33,388 --> 00:24:34,222
Later.

299
00:24:34,806 --> 00:24:36,391
No, let's talk now.

300
00:24:37,225 --> 00:24:40,270
Hey, Ro-mi. You little... That's so rude.

301
00:24:40,353 --> 00:24:41,980
-Stop it.
-Do you want a beating?

302
00:24:42,063 --> 00:24:43,440
Hey. Respond when someone talks to you.

303
00:24:43,523 --> 00:24:44,816
-Ro-mi.
-Okay.

304
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:47,569
Let's get ready. Take your seats.

305
00:24:51,865 --> 00:24:54,701
Why does the mood seem so dark?

306
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:59,539
Pil-sang? Why do you look the darkest?

307
00:25:00,165 --> 00:25:01,458
It... It wasn't me.

308
00:25:14,554 --> 00:25:15,597
Ro-mi.

309
00:25:18,141 --> 00:25:19,517
Why didn't you tell us that day?

310
00:25:19,601 --> 00:25:21,603
When you came from somewhere
when we were at the cafe,

311
00:25:21,686 --> 00:25:23,647
you took the level test that day, right?

312
00:25:24,064 --> 00:25:26,316
I felt awkward telling you then.

313
00:25:26,399 --> 00:25:28,693
You felt awkward because you felt guilty?

314
00:25:31,154 --> 00:25:32,656
In a way, yes.

315
00:25:32,739 --> 00:25:34,282
Since Hwi-yeong recommended me.

316
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:36,493
And since I could've failed the test,

317
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:38,245
I didn't think I had to tell you.

318
00:25:38,328 --> 00:25:41,414
But you passed anyway,
thanks to Hwi-yeong.

319
00:25:43,416 --> 00:25:45,168
I did pass.

320
00:25:46,169 --> 00:25:48,463
I think I passed
because I was good enough.

321
00:25:48,546 --> 00:25:50,715
I went over the test questions
when I got home,

322
00:25:50,799 --> 00:25:53,385
and I did pretty well on the test.

323
00:25:53,468 --> 00:25:54,594
It's so annoying.

324
00:25:54,844 --> 00:25:57,347
All this favor and preferential treatment.

325
00:25:57,430 --> 00:25:59,557
-It's not like that.
-That's enough.

326
00:25:59,641 --> 00:26:01,142
I don't want to talk to you.

327
00:26:02,310 --> 00:26:03,270
Ro-mi.

328
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,405
Did you two fight?

329
00:26:15,365 --> 00:26:16,449
Do you think I'm like you?

330
00:26:19,786 --> 00:26:21,788
Yes, we fought.

331
00:26:23,623 --> 00:26:24,708
Did you win?

332
00:26:28,503 --> 00:26:29,546
That means you won.

333
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:32,590
Losing is winning.

334
00:26:38,305 --> 00:26:40,557
That mask looks so bad on you.

335
00:26:47,856 --> 00:26:49,024
Yes.

336
00:26:49,607 --> 00:26:51,109
If possible,

337
00:26:51,192 --> 00:26:53,737
I'd like to meet
Jun-u's previous homeroom teacher.

338
00:26:54,487 --> 00:26:55,488
Yes.

339
00:26:56,489 --> 00:26:57,490
Hello?

340
00:26:59,284 --> 00:27:00,577
Please give me a call--

341
00:27:01,953 --> 00:27:02,954
What's his problem?

342
00:27:04,622 --> 00:27:06,875
Mr. Oh. A student asked me

343
00:27:06,958 --> 00:27:08,668
to bring this to you.

344
00:27:09,085 --> 00:27:10,920
-Thank you.
-Sure.

345
00:27:14,924 --> 00:27:16,801
SHIN JEONG-HU FROM BYEONGMUN HIGH

346
00:27:17,761 --> 00:27:19,471
"Shin Jeong-hu from Byeongmun High"?

347
00:27:21,556 --> 00:27:24,476
Excuse me. Did you just get this?

348
00:27:27,354 --> 00:27:28,480
Hey, Shin Jeong-hu!

349
00:27:29,189 --> 00:27:30,190
Hey!

350
00:27:30,648 --> 00:27:32,442
Jeong... Jeong-hu!

351
00:27:33,068 --> 00:27:37,322
Okay. Today, we will learn about cities.

352
00:27:37,405 --> 00:27:39,366
In our country, Seoul...

353
00:27:39,449 --> 00:27:41,159
Gas.

354
00:27:42,786 --> 00:27:44,913
Pil-sang, open the windows.

355
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:47,499
What was that?

356
00:27:48,958 --> 00:27:50,919
Jeong-hu! Hold on.

357
00:27:51,086 --> 00:27:52,295
-Hey, Shin Jeong-hu!
-Hey.

358
00:27:52,379 --> 00:27:53,880
What is Mr. Oh doing out there?

359
00:27:53,963 --> 00:27:55,757
-Why? What is it?
-Hey.

360
00:27:56,174 --> 00:27:57,884
Hey. Shin Jeong-hu!

361
00:27:58,635 --> 00:28:00,970
Hey! Shin Jeong-hu! Hold on. Wait.

362
00:28:01,388 --> 00:28:02,806
-Hey. Shin Jeong-hu!
-Jeong-hu?

363
00:28:02,889 --> 00:28:03,932
Hey!

364
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:06,393
Jun-u! Where are you going?
We're in the middle of class!

365
00:28:07,268 --> 00:28:08,937
What will I do with him?

366
00:28:09,854 --> 00:28:10,897
Teacher.

367
00:28:10,980 --> 00:28:13,316
Jeong-hu! Oh, cramp...

368
00:28:18,488 --> 00:28:20,657
Jun-u! Jun-u, Jeong-hu!

369
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:21,574
Jun-u!

370
00:28:24,869 --> 00:28:25,912
Hey!

371
00:28:40,677 --> 00:28:41,761
Thank you.

372
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:54,941
Can you lend me the bus fare?

373
00:28:57,986 --> 00:28:59,195
Don't you have to go back?

374
00:29:00,113 --> 00:29:01,281
I do.

375
00:29:02,115 --> 00:29:03,324
I'm in trouble now.

376
00:29:12,792 --> 00:29:14,836
You'll get expelled
if you're caught again.

377
00:29:14,919 --> 00:29:16,004
How will you handle it?

378
00:29:16,087 --> 00:29:17,505
But it's the first time for me.

379
00:29:17,839 --> 00:29:19,132
Don't you even feel angry?

380
00:29:19,758 --> 00:29:21,593
I just put the blame
for everything on you.

381
00:29:26,181 --> 00:29:27,015
Jeong-hu.

382
00:29:30,602 --> 00:29:31,728
Let's start over.

383
00:29:32,604 --> 00:29:34,522
At another school. Okay?

384
00:29:41,654 --> 00:29:42,947
I quit school.

385
00:29:46,451 --> 00:29:49,412
I'm just going to work instead
for the time being.

386
00:29:57,462 --> 00:29:58,296
Jun-u.

387
00:30:01,841 --> 00:30:03,051
I'm sorry for everything.

388
00:30:06,805 --> 00:30:08,473
You were falsely accused because of me

389
00:30:09,098 --> 00:30:10,475
and even forced to transfer.

390
00:30:12,811 --> 00:30:13,645
I'm sorry.

391
00:30:19,025 --> 00:30:20,235
I'm okay.

392
00:30:21,569 --> 00:30:23,321
I'm doing well here,
so that's enough for me.

393
00:30:25,114 --> 00:30:27,116
-Jun-u.
-What?

394
00:30:32,455 --> 00:30:33,289
Why?

395
00:30:34,374 --> 00:30:35,875
Is your new school okay?

396
00:30:37,335 --> 00:30:38,628
Yes, don't worry.

397
00:30:39,003 --> 00:30:40,839
Watch out for bullies at your school.

398
00:30:41,631 --> 00:30:42,757
You never know.

399
00:30:43,007 --> 00:30:44,133
I'm not afraid at all.

400
00:30:45,468 --> 00:30:49,180
You better call me
if someone else bullies you again.

401
00:30:49,681 --> 00:30:50,849
Don't talk like my big brother.

402
00:31:02,402 --> 00:31:03,820
I'll go to see you during summer break.

403
00:31:04,571 --> 00:31:05,822
You'll let me sleep over, right?

404
00:31:06,155 --> 00:31:07,282
Go back to school now.

405
00:31:10,285 --> 00:31:11,119
Jeong-hu.

406
00:31:15,123 --> 00:31:18,334
Our lives are not that messed up
after all.

407
00:31:20,879 --> 00:31:23,548
No. Who cares if we were born
a bit miserably?

408
00:31:23,798 --> 00:31:25,800
We can overcome it. Don't you think so?

409
00:31:30,221 --> 00:31:31,931
-I'll see you again.
-Bye.

410
00:31:34,851 --> 00:31:38,354
EXPRESS BUS
SEOUL TO UIJEONGBU

411
00:31:56,915 --> 00:31:58,625
And if you look here,

412
00:31:58,958 --> 00:32:00,627
their ownership of land was increased

413
00:32:00,710 --> 00:32:03,212
to contribute to their wealth...

414
00:32:05,632 --> 00:32:08,092
-Did you meet Jeong-hu?
-Yes.

415
00:32:08,593 --> 00:32:10,553
Jeong-hu gave me a letter.

416
00:32:10,637 --> 00:32:13,848
He said you were falsely accused
and forced to transfer because of him.

417
00:32:16,351 --> 00:32:18,144
My goodness.

418
00:32:18,561 --> 00:32:20,980
-What are you doing?
-Oh, yes, sir.

419
00:32:21,064 --> 00:32:22,982
I was having a word with Jun-u.

420
00:32:23,066 --> 00:32:25,860
He caught a cold without my permission.

421
00:32:30,531 --> 00:32:32,241
Keep coughing.

422
00:32:34,202 --> 00:32:37,830
The aristocrats consisted
mainly of high-ranking officials.

423
00:32:38,039 --> 00:32:39,874
And their government positions were

424
00:32:39,958 --> 00:32:42,251
inherited from one generation to the next.

425
00:32:42,710 --> 00:32:45,588
They enjoyed their wealth
and lived extravagantly.

426
00:32:45,797 --> 00:32:47,298
However, as time passed,

427
00:32:47,382 --> 00:32:50,259
they began to place more importance
on the National State Exam,

428
00:32:50,718 --> 00:32:53,304
and it started to change their lifestyles.

429
00:32:55,848 --> 00:32:57,016
Shall I change my seat?

430
00:32:58,101 --> 00:32:59,644
Thank you, Hwi-yeong.

431
00:33:01,062 --> 00:33:02,563
See you at the academy later, Soo-bin.

432
00:33:05,942 --> 00:33:07,568
-I'll call you later.
-Okay.

433
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:12,615
Ro-mi, aren't you going to practice?

434
00:33:12,699 --> 00:33:13,741
No.

435
00:33:13,825 --> 00:33:16,035
Ro-mi, I checked our script
one more time--

436
00:33:16,619 --> 00:33:18,371
Just memorize what I gave you.

437
00:33:18,454 --> 00:33:20,331
Ro-mi, watch your temper.

438
00:33:22,125 --> 00:33:23,960
You look like a bride
about to get married.

439
00:33:24,085 --> 00:33:26,337
Are you that happy to be
partners with O-je?

440
00:33:29,048 --> 00:33:30,133
Look at her lips.

441
00:33:30,383 --> 00:33:31,718
O-je, see you later.

442
00:33:32,218 --> 00:33:34,053
Okay, see you.

443
00:33:55,533 --> 00:33:57,201
Are you happy now?

444
00:33:59,537 --> 00:34:00,538
Yes.

445
00:34:01,539 --> 00:34:04,625
What did you talk about with Mr. Oh?

446
00:34:04,709 --> 00:34:06,002
You almost skipped the class.

447
00:34:09,005 --> 00:34:10,465
We didn't actually talk.

448
00:34:11,007 --> 00:34:12,175
Was it another matchup?

449
00:34:13,009 --> 00:34:14,010
No.

450
00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:19,265
Let's just say he protected me in a way.

451
00:34:19,432 --> 00:34:20,516
He covered for me.

452
00:34:22,226 --> 00:34:23,352
What are you talking about?

453
00:34:25,063 --> 00:34:26,439
Let's practice our English.

454
00:34:27,815 --> 00:34:29,233
Why don't we do it over there?

455
00:34:35,281 --> 00:34:36,115
What is that?

456
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:38,951
The sentences you wrote down for me.

457
00:34:40,161 --> 00:34:41,162
Okay.

458
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:42,580
Read them out loud.

459
00:34:44,791 --> 00:34:45,666
I'm embarrassed.

460
00:34:58,971 --> 00:35:01,724
Hang on. "So me"?

461
00:35:02,892 --> 00:35:05,812
It's "Some." Look carefully. S, O, M, E.

462
00:35:06,062 --> 00:35:07,522
Oh, right.

463
00:35:08,815 --> 00:35:10,191
I know this word.

464
00:35:10,399 --> 00:35:11,692
You know, but what?

465
00:35:13,486 --> 00:35:15,696
I'm a bit nervous.

466
00:35:17,198 --> 00:35:19,075
Okay. Read it again.

467
00:35:37,385 --> 00:35:40,930
Look at this word, "slept with."
You need to remember this.

468
00:35:41,013 --> 00:35:43,432
"Slept with." Don't pronounce it as
"sleep with."

469
00:35:43,599 --> 00:35:46,352
Just memorize these together.

470
00:35:46,769 --> 00:35:49,438
Don't forget to add "with" at the end
for the correct meaning.

471
00:35:51,774 --> 00:35:53,276
I knew that, you know.

472
00:35:55,111 --> 00:35:57,405
Is that so? What was "So me" then?

473
00:35:57,572 --> 00:35:58,656
"So me people"?

474
00:36:01,993 --> 00:36:03,035
The weather is great.

475
00:36:06,998 --> 00:36:10,251
But is this really your dream?

476
00:36:13,421 --> 00:36:14,547
Then what is your dream?

477
00:36:21,929 --> 00:36:22,930
Let's read it again.

478
00:36:23,014 --> 00:36:25,016
Since your part is more important
right now.

479
00:36:25,099 --> 00:36:26,934
All right, let me begin.

480
00:36:35,568 --> 00:36:37,361
You even added a touch of emotion.

481
00:36:39,113 --> 00:36:41,824
It seems like we're making some progress.

482
00:36:41,908 --> 00:36:43,159
I see a glimpse of hope.

483
00:36:46,454 --> 00:36:48,372
-To the academy?
-Yes.

484
00:36:49,624 --> 00:36:50,708
Bye.

485
00:36:52,168 --> 00:36:54,879
You have to practice that
really hard today.

486
00:36:54,962 --> 00:36:57,548
-Especially the spots I marked.
-Okay.

487
00:36:58,216 --> 00:36:59,300
You should go now.

488
00:37:05,765 --> 00:37:06,766
Wait.

489
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:18,319
Look. Every time you finish reading this,

490
00:37:18,402 --> 00:37:20,279
color in one grape, okay?

491
00:37:23,574 --> 00:37:24,408
Grape?

492
00:37:27,119 --> 00:37:29,121
One, two, three, four...

493
00:37:32,124 --> 00:37:33,292
Fifty times?

494
00:37:34,085 --> 00:37:36,254
You know 50 times isn't enough, right?

495
00:37:40,591 --> 00:37:41,842
Do you want ten more?

496
00:37:43,970 --> 00:37:45,012
This is enough.

497
00:37:47,890 --> 00:37:49,558
-You should get going.
-Okay.

498
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:53,145
Study hard! Stay up all night!

499
00:38:04,115 --> 00:38:05,074
Hi, Mom. What's up?

500
00:38:05,157 --> 00:38:06,701
Soo-bin, is it true?

501
00:38:07,076 --> 00:38:08,869
-What?
-Did you partner up with the guy

502
00:38:08,953 --> 00:38:10,621
who was forced to transfer recently?

503
00:38:10,871 --> 00:38:13,165
What is wrong with Mr. Oh?

504
00:38:13,332 --> 00:38:15,251
Does he think
that the test is a joke or what?

505
00:38:15,334 --> 00:38:17,336
How could he partner you up
with a guy like that?

506
00:38:17,420 --> 00:38:19,714
It wasn't Mr. Oh.

507
00:38:19,797 --> 00:38:21,132
We did a random draw.

508
00:38:21,215 --> 00:38:22,341
A random draw?

509
00:38:23,592 --> 00:38:25,594
It was my idea, Mom.

510
00:38:25,678 --> 00:38:27,805
It's a test. How could your partner
be decided like that?

511
00:38:27,888 --> 00:38:30,391
Hey. Soo-bin?

512
00:38:34,645 --> 00:38:35,688
Hello.

513
00:38:37,315 --> 00:38:38,441
Jun-u.

514
00:38:39,108 --> 00:38:40,735
Jun-u.

515
00:38:40,818 --> 00:38:42,111
Jun-u.

516
00:38:45,364 --> 00:38:46,198
Jun-u...

517
00:38:51,454 --> 00:38:53,789
I knew it.

518
00:38:53,956 --> 00:38:56,667
I bet you were pretending to be
washing your hair to cover this.

519
00:38:56,834 --> 00:38:57,877
Let me see.

520
00:38:58,461 --> 00:39:00,046
Gosh, my goodness.

521
00:39:02,256 --> 00:39:03,299
Mom.

522
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:05,426
How did you know?

523
00:39:05,885 --> 00:39:09,472
Hey, Yeong-bae. Don't you know
that all moms know everything?

524
00:39:09,638 --> 00:39:12,058
They have crazy instincts.
They can practically read your mind.

525
00:39:12,141 --> 00:39:14,352
Gosh, you shouldn't have lied to your mom.

526
00:39:15,811 --> 00:39:18,147
What are you going to do now?

527
00:39:18,898 --> 00:39:20,816
Gosh, this is so upsetting.

528
00:39:24,403 --> 00:39:26,405
It's okay. It wasn't a big deal.

529
00:39:27,239 --> 00:39:30,284
You're sure, right?
Nothing serious is going on?

530
00:39:30,409 --> 00:39:32,536
Yes, I'm sure. It's all been sorted out.

531
00:39:35,790 --> 00:39:37,958
I went through hoops
to get you out of that situation.

532
00:39:42,671 --> 00:39:44,006
Trust me, Mom.

533
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:48,386
You said I'm the only person
you can trust in the whole world.

534
00:39:52,098 --> 00:39:55,559
Nothing bad will happen. Trust me, okay?

